component.name: NetworkManager
component.description: NetworkManager is a system service that manages network interfaces and connections based on user or automatic configuration. It supports Ethernet, Bridge, Bond, VLAN, Team, InfiniBand, Wi-Fi, mobile broadband (WWAN), PPPoE and other devices, and supports a variety of different VPN services.

components.name: NetworkManager-dispatcher-routing-rules
components.description: This adds a NetworkManager dispatcher file to support networking configurations using "/etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/rule-NAME" files (eg, to do policy-based routing).

components.name: NetworkManager-initscripts-updown
components.description: Installs alternative ifup/ifdown scripts that talk to NetworkManager. This is only for backward compatibility with initscripts (network-scripts). Preferably use nmcli instead.

components.name: NetworkManager-config-connectivity-redhat
components.description: This adds a NetworkManager configuration file to enable connectivity checking via Red Hat infrastructure.

components.name: NetworkManager-config-server
components.description: This adds a NetworkManager configuration file to make it behave more like the old "network" service. In particular, it stops NetworkManager from automatically running DHCP on unconfigured ethernet devices, and allows connections with static IP addresses to be brought up even on ethernet devices with no carrier. This package is intended to be installed by default for server deployments.
